## 1. Crop Diagnosis & Image Upload

> The core feature of ZARii AI. A farmer uploads a leaf photo, gets a disease diagnosis. The admin monitors all diagnoses, flags bad ones, and tracks AI accuracy.

---

### 1-A — "Analyze now" works without a photo selected
**Severity:** 🟠 Broken (user-side)

**What the farmer sees:**
On the Analyze page, clicking the green "Analyze now" button when no photo has been chosen doesn't give any error — it silently runs a fake demo diagnosis (Early Blight, 94% confidence). The farmer thinks they got a real result from nothing.

**What the admin sees:**
The Diagnoses tab gets a scan record with `ai_provider: 'mock'` and no `image_url`. This pollutes the diagnosis history with meaningless records that the admin cannot distinguish from real ones.

**Root cause:** `startAnalysis()` in `Analyze.jsx` has no guard checking `if (!selectedFile)` before calling the API.

**Fix status:** ✅ Fixed — button now shows validation error "Please upload a leaf photo first"

**Files:** `frontend-assets/components/Analyze.jsx` → `startAnalysis()` | `backend/routes/diagnose.js`

---

### 1-B — Failed real diagnosis shows same screen as demo example
**Severity:** 🟡 Misleading (user-side + admin-side)

**What the farmer sees:**
If the real AI call fails (server error, timeout), the result screen shows "Early Blight — 94% confidence — Antracol 70 WP ₨1,180" — the exact same hardcoded example that demo mode shows. The farmer has no way to know whether this is a real result or a fallback. They might go buy Antracol based on a fake diagnosis.

**What the admin sees:**
No scan record is created when the API fails before the DB insert. So the Diagnoses tab has no record of the failure. The admin cannot see how often AI calls are failing or what farmers were shown when they failed.

**Root cause:** `ResultView` in `Analyze.jsx` — when `!diagnosis && diagError`, it shows an error screen. But when `diagnosis?._isDemo` is true AND there's a real error, both fall through to the same hardcoded demo data block.

**Fix status:** 🟠 Open

**Files:** `frontend-assets/components/Analyze.jsx` → `ResultView` L254–277 | `backend/routes/diagnose.js`

---

### 1-C — "Flag" button on diagnoses does nothing
**Severity:** 🟠 Broken (admin-side only)

**What the admin sees:**
Every row in the Diagnoses tab has a "Flag" button — meant to mark a suspicious AI result for agronomist review. The button renders correctly but clicking it does absolutely nothing. No API call is made.

**What the farmer sees:**
Nothing directly. But unflagged bad diagnoses stay in the system unchallenged, and farmers who gave negative feedback (👎) never get their scan reviewed.

**Root cause:** The "Flag" button in `DiagnosesTab` in `Admin.jsx` has no `onClick` handler.

**Backend:** `POST /api/admin/diagnoses/:id/flag` exists and works correctly (toggles `flagged` field). The backend is complete — only the button is missing its handler.

**Fix status:** 🟠 Open

**Files:** `frontend-assets/components/Admin.jsx` → `DiagnosesTab` flag button | `backend/routes/admin/diagnoses.js` L40–49

